00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:24.600
in this room, and
very ambitious,

00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:26.930
and goals and results-oriented.

00:02:26.930 --> 00:02:27.920
So yes.

00:02:27.920 --> 00:02:31.920
So before we talk about why
meditation is the new caffeine,

00:02:31.920 --> 00:02:34.600
I think that we have to
look a little bit deeper

00:02:34.600 --> 00:02:36.810
into what caffeine does
to our nervous system

00:02:36.810 --> 00:02:39.550
and what meditation does
to our nervous system

00:02:39.550 --> 00:02:42.770
because interestingly, there
are quite a few similarities.

00:02:42.770 --> 00:02:45.590
Both will make you
feel more energetic.

00:02:45.590 --> 00:02:47.710
Both can make you
more productive.

00:02:47.710 --> 00:02:49.870
You have to do both
of them every day.

00:02:49.870 --> 00:02:53.202
You have to stop the inertia
of your day, to do both.

00:02:53.202 --> 00:02:55.160
So you know, Jerry Seinfeld
has been practicing

00:02:55.160 --> 00:02:57.640
the same style of meditation
that I teach for 40 years.

00:02:57.640 --> 00:03:01.782
And he likens it to a cellphone
charger for your mind and body.

00:03:01.782 --> 00:03:03.740
He's like, you meditate,
and on the other side,

00:03:03.740 --> 00:03:06.270
you come out more
refreshed, more recharged.

00:03:06.270 --> 00:03:10.930
So this is what it can feel
like, after we drink caffeine.

00:03:10.930 --> 00:03:12.540
So as I was preparing
for this talk,

00:03:12.540 --> 00:03:14.450
I did quite a bit of
research on exactly what

00:03:14.450 --> 00:03:15.700
caffeine is doing to the body.

00:03:15.700 --> 00:03:18.246
And some of the
things surprised me.

00:03:18.246 --> 00:03:19.870
I thought that caffeine
was just simply

00:03:19.870 --> 00:03:21.930
a stimulant, that it
just sort of stimulated

00:03:21.930 --> 00:03:23.420
your nervous system and
that's the reason that you

00:03:23.420 --> 00:03:24.253
got more productive.

00:03:24.253 --> 00:03:26.200
But it's not as simple as that.

00:03:26.200 --> 00:03:29.460
Molecularly, caffeine is very
similar to a chemical called

00:03:29.460 --> 00:03:30.770
adenosine.

00:03:30.770 --> 00:03:32.972
Now, adenosine is the thing
that your brain produces

00:03:32.972 --> 00:03:35.180
throughout the day-- which
is what makes you sleepy--

00:03:35.180 --> 00:03:36.690
and is the thing
that cues you to go

00:03:36.690 --> 00:03:38.420
to bed at the end of the night.

00:03:38.420 --> 00:03:42.247
So when you ingest caffeine,
these caffeine molecules

00:03:42.247 --> 00:03:43.830
are very similar to
adenosine, so they

00:03:43.830 --> 00:03:46.270
block your brain's
adenosine receptors.

00:03:46.270 --> 00:03:49.550
So it disallows your brain
from knowing that you're tired,

00:03:49.550 --> 00:03:51.120
which is why you're
able to do more.

00:03:51.120 --> 00:03:52.870
You know, mid-afternoon,
you're like, oof,

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:53.670
I've got to take a nap.

00:03:53.670 --> 00:03:54.630
But you're like, I don't
have time to take a nap,

00:03:54.630 --> 00:03:56.171
so let me drink some
coffee, instead.

00:03:56.171 --> 00:03:58.050
And then you're
able to power out.

00:03:58.050 --> 00:03:59.452
Sounds good so far, right?

00:03:59.452 --> 00:04:01.410
But now we've got to talk
about the differences

00:04:01.410 --> 00:04:04.850
between meditation and caffeine.

00:04:04.850 --> 00:04:07.630
Caffeine is essentially
artificially hijacking

00:04:07.630 --> 00:04:08.760
your nervous system.

00:04:08.760 --> 00:04:11.290
It's disallowing you from
feeling how tired you

00:04:11.290 --> 00:04:14.480
are because that caffeine
is mimicking that adenosine

00:04:14.480 --> 00:04:17.250
and blocking those receptors
in your brain, which is not

00:04:17.250 --> 00:04:19.329
that bad for you,
in and of itself.

00:04:19.329 --> 00:04:21.390
It's not hurting you
while it's happening.

00:04:21.390 --> 00:04:23.520
But the other thing
that caffeine does

00:04:23.520 --> 00:04:26.500
is that it stimulates more
neural activity in the brain.

00:04:26.500 --> 00:04:30.360
And when your pituitary
gland notices this increase

00:04:30.360 --> 00:04:32.310
in neural activity,
it thinks that there's

00:04:32.310 --> 00:04:34.120
some sort of an
emergency happening.

00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:36.150
And so it triggers
your adrenal glands

00:04:36.150 --> 00:04:39.030
to start releasing adrenalin.

00:04:39.030 --> 00:04:40.750
And as you guys probably
know, adrenaline

00:04:40.750 --> 00:04:42.170
is the number one
stress chemical

00:04:42.170 --> 00:04:44.670
that gets released in your body
when you launch into a fight

00:04:44.670 --> 00:04:47.180
or flight stress reaction.

00:04:47.180 --> 00:04:49.399
So basically, caffeine will
make you more productive.

00:04:49.399 --> 00:04:50.940
It will make you
feel more energized.

00:04:50.940 --> 00:04:52.655
But there's quite a cost
that you have to pay.

00:04:52.655 --> 00:04:54.610
There's quite a price that
you have to pay for that.

00:04:54.610 --> 00:04:56.160
And really, that's
the come down.

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:57.312
So you drink too
much coffee, and you

00:04:57.312 --> 00:04:59.050
start to get the
nervous shakes, right?

00:04:59.050 --> 00:05:01.120
Or afterwards, you
feel even more tired

00:05:01.120 --> 00:05:02.840
than you were
before you started?

00:05:02.840 --> 00:05:06.040
This is really the
price that we pay.

00:05:06.040 --> 00:05:08.330
I liken the human
body to a casino--

00:05:08.330 --> 00:05:09.830
you can cheat it
for a little while.

00:05:09.830 --> 00:05:11.450
You can come out ahead
for a little while,

00:05:11.450 --> 00:05:12.970
but ultimately,
the house is always

00:05:12.970 --> 00:05:14.900
going to win because
your body is,

00:05:14.900 --> 00:05:17.140
in fact, a perfect accountant.

00:05:17.140 --> 00:05:18.930
So now let's talk
about what meditation

00:05:18.930 --> 00:05:20.110
is doing to the body.

00:05:20.110 --> 00:05:20.610
Excuse me.

00:05:23.860 --> 00:05:27.210
I think I have a little
adrenalin going right now.

00:05:27.210 --> 00:05:28.960
I talk really fast
about meditation,

00:05:28.960 --> 00:05:31.520
and you get a little dry mouth.

00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:34.530
So meditation will also
make you more productive.

00:05:34.530 --> 00:05:35.800
And it will also energize you.

00:05:35.800 --> 00:05:38.190
But it does it very
differently than caffeine does.

00:05:38.190 --> 00:05:40.190
What meditation does is
that it gives your body

00:05:40.190 --> 00:05:42.500
rest that is arguably
somewhere between two

00:05:42.500 --> 00:05:45.230
to five times deeper than sleep.

00:05:45.230 --> 00:05:46.890
So this is not an
insignificant point.

00:05:46.890 --> 00:05:48.270
When you meditate,
you're giving your body

00:05:48.270 --> 00:05:50.440
rest that is somewhere
between two to five times

00:05:50.440 --> 00:05:52.240
deeper than sleep.

00:05:52.240 --> 00:05:54.510
And when you give your
body that deep rest,

00:05:54.510 --> 00:05:57.150
you're essentially de-exciting
your nervous system.

00:05:57.150 --> 00:06:00.155
And when you de-excite
something, you create order.

00:06:00.155 --> 00:06:02.030
When you create order
in your nervous system,

00:06:02.030 --> 00:06:04.280
then all of those stresses
that we've been picking up,

00:06:04.280 --> 00:06:05.870
through our decades
of overachieving,

00:06:05.870 --> 00:06:07.930
can start to leave the building.

00:06:07.930 --> 00:06:10.760
So imagine that you have a
pot of water on the stove.

00:06:10.760 --> 00:06:12.970
If you turn up the heat
on that pot of water,

00:06:12.970 --> 00:06:14.800
and you excite the
molecules, they're

00:06:14.800 --> 00:06:16.300
going to start to
move very quickly.

00:06:16.300 --> 00:06:18.180
And if you're trying to
extract something out

00:06:18.180 --> 00:06:20.620
of that pot of boiling water, so
you have like a grain of rice--

00:06:20.620 --> 00:06:22.350
PS, the grain of rice
represents stress

00:06:22.350 --> 00:06:25.000
in this analogy-- you're
trying to pull that stress out

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:25.959
of the pot of water.

00:06:25.959 --> 00:06:28.250
When it's excited and the
molecules are moving quickly,

00:06:28.250 --> 00:06:30.040
it's very hard to do that.

00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:32.090
When you meditate, you
de-excite the body.

00:06:32.090 --> 00:06:34.040
So it's like cooling
down that water.

00:06:34.040 --> 00:06:36.150
It's de-exciting the
molecules in that water.

00:06:36.150 --> 00:06:37.780
So imagine it was almost frozen.

00:06:37.780 --> 00:06:39.990
It would be sort of slushy,
and you could easily

00:06:39.990 --> 00:06:43.490
go in and detect that rice
and pull it out of the water.

00:06:43.490 --> 00:06:44.990
Same thing with
stress in our body--

00:06:44.990 --> 00:06:47.120
we meditate, we give
our body that deep rest,

00:06:47.120 --> 00:06:50.230
de-excite our nervous system,
and it's easier for stress

00:06:50.230 --> 00:06:52.550
to leave the body,
which is one of the ways

00:06:52.550 --> 00:06:54.850
that meditation makes
us more productive.

00:06:54.850 --> 00:06:57.310
Contrary to popular
belief, your stress

00:06:57.310 --> 00:06:59.860
is not helping you in the
productivity or performance

00:06:59.860 --> 00:07:00.360
department.

00:07:00.360 --> 00:07:03.010
I'll talk more about
that in a moment.

00:07:03.010 --> 00:07:04.690
But what I'm
interested in right now

00:07:04.690 --> 00:07:07.012
is really talking
about the rest.

00:07:07.012 --> 00:07:08.970
If you're resting two to
five times deeper than

00:07:08.970 --> 00:07:10.970
sleep when you meditate,
then when you come out

00:07:10.970 --> 00:07:14.710
of that meditation, then you
are, in fact, more awake.

00:07:14.710 --> 00:07:16.720
A 20 minute meditation
is basically

00:07:16.720 --> 00:07:19.420
the equivalent of doing an
hour or an hour and a half nap,

00:07:19.420 --> 00:07:21.099
but you don't have
the sleep hangover.

00:07:21.099 --> 00:07:23.265
So you go into meditation,
give your body that rest,

00:07:23.265 --> 00:07:25.270
and when you come out,
you're more awake.

00:07:25.270 --> 00:07:27.510
You are, in fact,
more conscious.

00:07:27.510 --> 00:07:30.270
And a few of the attributes
of having more consciousness

00:07:30.270 --> 00:07:31.930
are the ability to
hold many things

00:07:31.930 --> 00:07:34.440
in one awareness,
the ability to detect

00:07:34.440 --> 00:07:37.320
subtlety-- subtle differences
in things-- and the ability

00:07:37.320 --> 00:07:39.580
to detect themes, all
of which are going

00:07:39.580 --> 00:07:42.990
to make you more productive,
but in a sustainable way

00:07:42.990 --> 00:07:46.020
versus the way caffeine does it,
which is just costing your body

00:07:46.020 --> 00:07:47.410
a little bit more.

00:07:47.410 --> 00:07:49.500
Now, PS, I should
say that I'm not here

00:07:49.500 --> 00:07:51.660
to, like, give anybody
any rules or be like,

00:07:51.660 --> 00:07:52.590
put away that coffee.

00:07:52.590 --> 00:07:54.964
You're like, damnit, why did
I bring coffee to this talk?

00:07:56.890 --> 00:07:59.480
My personal philosophy
on drugs are

00:07:59.480 --> 00:08:02.350
that if the pros outweigh
the cons, then enjoy.

00:08:02.350 --> 00:08:04.277
Right?

00:08:04.277 --> 00:08:05.860
But I just think we
have to understand

00:08:05.860 --> 00:08:07.990
what the pros and
what the cons are

00:08:07.990 --> 00:08:10.550
and what they're costing us.

00:08:10.550 --> 00:08:12.720
Oh, and PS, there
are some monks that

00:08:12.720 --> 00:08:14.910
have been experimenting
with coffee and meditation

00:08:14.910 --> 00:08:17.220
for hundreds if not
thousands of years.

00:08:17.220 --> 00:08:20.210
Some people report that I'll
drink coffee before I meditate,

00:08:20.210 --> 00:08:23.490
and it proves to be a really
fascinating experience.

00:08:23.490 --> 00:08:26.680
Now, this is dependent
almost entirely

00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:29.359
on what kind of meditation
that you practice,

00:08:29.359 --> 00:08:30.775
which leads me to
our second point

00:08:30.775 --> 00:08:32.358
that we're going to
cover today, which

00:08:32.358 --> 00:08:34.169
is the differences
between the two most

00:08:34.169 --> 00:08:36.255
