00:26:34.230 --> 00:26:35.915
Good.

00:26:35.915 --> 00:26:38.040
So this will be our final
point, before we actually

00:26:38.040 --> 00:26:39.740
try some meditation.

00:26:39.740 --> 00:26:43.590
And it is how to not
let your goals get

00:26:43.590 --> 00:26:46.490
in the way of your
success because again, I

00:26:46.490 --> 00:26:48.710
imagine that you guys are
all very ambitious, very

00:26:48.710 --> 00:26:52.390
results-oriented, very
career and goal-oriented,

00:26:52.390 --> 00:26:54.140
which is great.

00:26:54.140 --> 00:26:57.290
However, the trick here is
that we can have a tendency

00:26:57.290 --> 00:27:01.070
to delay our happiness or
delay our self care until we've

00:27:01.070 --> 00:27:03.206
accomplished that
one final thing,

00:27:03.206 --> 00:27:05.580
just until we get that one
more zero in our bank account,

00:27:05.580 --> 00:27:07.090
and we just finish
this one project,

00:27:07.090 --> 00:27:09.080
or I just hire this
one more employee,

00:27:09.080 --> 00:27:10.620
then I'll start
going to the gym.

00:27:10.620 --> 00:27:12.890
I'm going to start meditating
as soon as I finish

00:27:12.890 --> 00:27:15.210
this giant project that
my boss needs from me,

00:27:15.210 --> 00:27:19.820
I am going to take a
vacation as soon as I make

00:27:19.820 --> 00:27:23.960
this amount of money, and that
the main themes that we delay

00:27:23.960 --> 00:27:27.230
our happiness for
are money, education,

00:27:27.230 --> 00:27:28.990
and romantic relationships.

00:27:28.990 --> 00:27:31.120
We think, well, as soon
as I have enough zeros,

00:27:31.120 --> 00:27:33.200
then I'll be happy-- as soon
as I have the perfect job,

00:27:33.200 --> 00:27:35.741
then I will be happy-- as soon
as I have the perfect partner,

00:27:35.741 --> 00:27:36.810
then I will be happy.

00:27:36.810 --> 00:27:38.390
But as Carrie
Bradshaw so eloquently

00:27:38.390 --> 00:27:39.840
said in "Sex and
the City," you're

00:27:39.840 --> 00:27:42.130
only going to have two out of
the three in New York City.

00:27:42.130 --> 00:27:43.095
You're either going to
have the perfect boyfriend,

00:27:43.095 --> 00:27:44.610
or the perfect job,
and no apartment,

00:27:44.610 --> 00:27:46.890
or the perfect apartment,
perfect job, but no boyfriend,

00:27:46.890 --> 00:27:49.140
but you're never going to
have three out of the three.

00:27:49.140 --> 00:27:51.760
So if you're waiting to
have all three to be happy,

00:27:51.760 --> 00:27:54.400
it's going to be a
really long wait.

00:27:54.400 --> 00:27:56.440
My analogy, here,
is like, imagine

00:27:56.440 --> 00:27:58.960
that you're sitting at
the bottom of a mountain,

00:27:58.960 --> 00:27:59.820
and you're looking
at this mountain

00:27:59.820 --> 00:28:00.620
that you want to climb.

00:28:00.620 --> 00:28:01.880
You're like, OK, I'm going
to do it because once

00:28:01.880 --> 00:28:03.210
I get the top of
this mountain, then

00:28:03.210 --> 00:28:04.430
I will have achieved success.

00:28:04.430 --> 00:28:05.751
Then I can be proud of myself.

00:28:05.751 --> 00:28:07.750
Then I will have validated
myself to my parents,

00:28:07.750 --> 00:28:09.874
and they can justify that
expensive college tuition

00:28:09.874 --> 00:28:11.110
that they paid for.

00:28:11.110 --> 00:28:12.940
So we start climbing
the mountain.

00:28:12.940 --> 00:28:14.740
And then we get to
the top of a mountain,

00:28:14.740 --> 00:28:16.000
and we're still not happy.

00:28:16.000 --> 00:28:18.570
We still don't have the ability
to access this present moment

00:28:18.570 --> 00:28:19.310
awareness.

00:28:19.310 --> 00:28:21.957
And now we've proven to ourself
that we can climb the mountain.

00:28:21.957 --> 00:28:23.665
And now we see all of
the other mountains

00:28:23.665 --> 00:28:24.834
that we have yet to climb.

00:28:24.834 --> 00:28:26.500
So then we think, oh,
well, my happiness

00:28:26.500 --> 00:28:28.410
must be at the top of
this next mountain.

00:28:28.410 --> 00:28:29.535
So we start climbing again.

00:28:29.535 --> 00:28:31.826
Get to the top of this
mountain, you're like, oh, crap,

00:28:31.826 --> 00:28:32.800
I'm still not happy.

00:28:32.800 --> 00:28:34.760
More and more mountains
that we can climb.

00:28:34.760 --> 00:28:37.410
And so this can sort
of go on indefinitely.

00:28:37.410 --> 00:28:40.010
So I would suggest that instead
of waiting until you finish

00:28:40.010 --> 00:28:42.030
your To Do list to
be happy, instead

00:28:42.030 --> 00:28:44.310
of waiting until you've
accomplished all of your goals

00:28:44.310 --> 00:28:46.650
to give yourself permission
to take care of yourself,

00:28:46.650 --> 00:28:49.500
what if you start taking
care of yourself now?

00:28:49.500 --> 00:28:52.380
What if you give yourself access
to your bliss and fulfillment

00:28:52.380 --> 00:28:55.180
inside of you, start
your day with that,

00:28:55.180 --> 00:28:58.240
and then use your To Do
list, use your desires

00:28:58.240 --> 00:29:00.780
as an indicator of how
and where to deliver

00:29:00.780 --> 00:29:02.750
your gifts to the world?

00:29:02.750 --> 00:29:04.020
Sounds a little hippy dippy.

00:29:04.020 --> 00:29:05.330
Sounds a little esoteric.

00:29:05.330 --> 00:29:08.449
But just try it out,
and see what happens.

00:29:08.449 --> 00:29:09.990
My personal experience,
and what I've

00:29:09.990 --> 00:29:12.705
seen from my over 700 clients
that I've taught to meditate,

00:29:12.705 --> 00:29:15.080
is that when you start to
approach life and this attitude

00:29:15.080 --> 00:29:17.400
of what can I give,
then life starts

00:29:17.400 --> 00:29:18.700
giving you a lot more back.

00:29:18.700 --> 00:29:21.050
Instead of going into life
with like a what can I get

00:29:21.050 --> 00:29:24.060
and being needly attached
to, well, this person

00:29:24.060 --> 00:29:26.250
has to show up, or else--
or I have to get this job,

00:29:26.250 --> 00:29:28.125
or else-- or you have
to ask me to marry you,

00:29:28.125 --> 00:29:29.990
or else-- or I have
to get this job,

00:29:29.990 --> 00:29:32.660
or I'm not good enough,
this-- it's very hard for life

00:29:32.660 --> 00:29:35.840
to show up when you've got a
death grip on your desires.

00:29:35.840 --> 00:29:41.140
And if you insert a meditation
practice or some really solid

00:29:41.140 --> 00:29:43.020
self care and stress
relieving techniques

00:29:43.020 --> 00:29:45.500
into your day,
every day, then you

00:29:45.500 --> 00:29:48.120
are quite innocently and
quite spontaneously going

00:29:48.120 --> 00:29:51.580
to start approaching your life
from a place of fulfillment--

00:29:51.580 --> 00:29:54.130
what can I give to this
versus what can I get.

00:29:54.130 --> 00:29:56.810
And what happens is this
beautiful, reciprocal

00:29:56.810 --> 00:29:57.690
upward spiral.

