Yes?

00:30:07.380 --> 00:30:10.206
AUDIENCE: Before, you contrasted
[INAUDIBLE] meditations.

00:30:10.206 --> 00:30:11.299
So where does yoga fit in?

00:30:11.299 --> 00:30:12.090
EMILY FLETCHER: Ah.

00:30:12.090 --> 00:30:13.130
Thanks for asking.

00:30:13.130 --> 00:30:18.040
So I think I teach Vedic
meditation, V-E-D-I-C.

00:30:18.040 --> 00:30:21.130
It comes from the Sanskrit word,
Veda, which means knowledge.

00:30:21.130 --> 00:30:22.220
Knowledge of what?

00:30:22.220 --> 00:30:23.570
Knowledge of nature.

00:30:23.570 --> 00:30:25.440
So it's basically
like using natural law

00:30:25.440 --> 00:30:27.450
to help us get to
where we want to go.

00:30:27.450 --> 00:30:28.970
You know, you
de-excite your body,

00:30:28.970 --> 00:30:35.580
you start to access the place
from which we get our desires.

00:30:35.580 --> 00:30:38.420
Yoga-- so Vedic meditation
comes from the Vedas.

00:30:38.420 --> 00:30:40.210
The Vedas is an ancient
body of knowledge,

00:30:40.210 --> 00:30:42.247
like 5 or 6,000 years old.

00:30:42.247 --> 00:30:44.080
And the Vedas are the
same body of knowledge

00:30:44.080 --> 00:30:48.160
that give us yoga,
acupuncture, feng shui,

00:30:48.160 --> 00:30:50.000
and Ayurvedic medicine,
Ayurvedic cooking.

00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:52.410
They all come from the same
ancient body of knowledge.

00:30:52.410 --> 00:30:55.215
So yoga is basically,
you know, those series of

00:30:55.215 --> 00:30:57.340
poses that you move through.

00:30:57.340 --> 00:30:58.800
It's called an asana practice.

00:30:58.800 --> 00:31:01.790
And asana is a Sanskrit
word that means seat.

00:31:01.790 --> 00:31:04.614
So if you take a yoga class,
I mean, there's chair pose,

00:31:04.614 --> 00:31:06.280
but then there's all
those other asanas.

00:31:06.280 --> 00:31:07.740
And they're all called seat.

00:31:07.740 --> 00:31:09.660
So why is that?

00:31:09.660 --> 00:31:11.450
Ardha candraasana, Trikonasana.

00:31:11.450 --> 00:31:15.290
So all of them, each asana,
somewhere in the word,

00:31:15.290 --> 00:31:16.730
has the word seat.

00:31:16.730 --> 00:31:17.290
Why is that?

00:31:17.290 --> 00:31:20.420
Because each of those
poses is preparing the body

00:31:20.420 --> 00:31:22.190
to become a seat
for consciousness

00:31:22.190 --> 00:31:23.630
to come and sit in.

00:31:23.630 --> 00:31:26.220
And actually, yoga was
designed for teenage boys who

00:31:26.220 --> 00:31:27.645
couldn't sit still and meditate.

00:31:27.645 --> 00:31:29.770
So they would move them
through this asana practice

00:31:29.770 --> 00:31:30.780
so that they could meditate.

00:31:30.780 --> 00:31:32.930
So yoga was actually
designed to prepare the body

00:31:32.930 --> 00:31:36.180
for meditation, which I think
is so beautiful because yoga,

00:31:36.180 --> 00:31:38.200
obviously, has gotten
so popular in the West,

00:31:38.200 --> 00:31:41.850
and I think it's really paved
the way for this new meditation

00:31:41.850 --> 00:31:43.810
awakening that is happening.

00:31:43.810 --> 00:31:46.260
But I think that the combination
of yoga and meditation,

00:31:46.260 --> 00:31:50.360
specifically this style,
is really beautiful.

00:31:50.360 --> 00:31:51.250
Thanks for asking.

