00:36:27.044 --> 00:36:29.210
and checking your heart
rate, your body temperature,

00:36:29.210 --> 00:36:31.376
and how much movement you
have throughout the night.

00:36:31.376 --> 00:36:33.530
So it can actually tell
you how deep your sleep is.

00:36:33.530 --> 00:36:37.550
And I have a kind of cool
story from a client in LA.

00:36:37.550 --> 00:36:38.870
He had one of those bracelets.

00:36:38.870 --> 00:36:41.240
And his sleeping pattern,
before he took my course,

00:36:41.240 --> 00:36:45.090
it used to go light, medium,
deep, wake up for 18 minutes,

00:36:45.090 --> 00:36:49.030
light, medium, deep, wake up
for 18 minutes, medium, wake up.

00:36:49.030 --> 00:36:51.100
And that took him about
eight or nine hours.

00:36:51.100 --> 00:36:52.280
And then the bracelet broke.

00:36:52.280 --> 00:36:53.680
And he took the
meditation class.

00:36:53.680 --> 00:36:55.107
And then he got it back.

00:36:55.107 --> 00:36:56.940
And then, after about
10 days of meditating,

00:36:56.940 --> 00:36:58.360
he tracked his sleep again.

00:36:58.360 --> 00:37:00.910
And his sleep pattern
went light, medium, deep,

00:37:00.910 --> 00:37:04.210
for six hours, medium,
light, wake up.

00:37:04.210 --> 00:37:07.200
So he actually shaved three
hours off of his sleeping time.

00:37:07.200 --> 00:37:09.550
But he would wake up
rested because his sleep

00:37:09.550 --> 00:37:11.070
became more efficient.

00:37:11.070 --> 00:37:12.570
So this is one of
the main arguments

00:37:12.570 --> 00:37:14.950
I make to people who say, I
don't have time to meditate.

00:37:14.950 --> 00:37:17.200
The practice that I teach
is 20 minutes, twice a day,

00:37:17.200 --> 00:37:19.010
so it's a 40 minute investment.

00:37:19.010 --> 00:37:20.810
Well, if you're shaving
even one hour off

00:37:20.810 --> 00:37:22.940
of your sleep at night, because
your sleep is more efficient,

00:37:22.940 --> 00:37:24.630
then you're already
in the black.

00:37:24.630 --> 00:37:25.450
Right?

00:37:25.450 --> 00:37:28.531
The return investment is already
higher than what you're making.

00:37:28.531 --> 00:37:31.030
And that's not even to speak
of the increase in productivity

00:37:31.030 --> 00:37:34.045
or the happiness or any
of that kind of things.

00:37:34.045 --> 00:37:36.780
And so it's different
for everyone,

00:37:36.780 --> 00:37:39.020
but there actually
are physical things

00:37:39.020 --> 00:37:40.720
that you can plug
into your phone

00:37:40.720 --> 00:37:42.690
and track your own progress.

00:37:42.690 --> 00:37:45.670
But ultimately, it's do I have
a little bit more patience?

00:37:45.670 --> 00:37:48.230
Do I have a little bit more joy?

00:37:48.230 --> 00:37:50.174
Are my listening skills
a little bit better?

00:37:50.174 --> 00:37:51.840
Am I enjoying my life
a little bit more?

00:37:51.840 --> 00:37:54.409
Do I feel like I have a
little bit more to give?

00:37:54.409 --> 00:37:55.950
We want to judge
the meditation based

00:37:55.950 --> 00:37:58.290
on how we're performing
in our waking state,

00:37:58.290 --> 00:38:00.610
not how many or few
thoughts we have

00:38:00.610 --> 00:38:03.320
when we meditate, which
leads me to the number one

00:38:03.320 --> 00:38:05.090
misconception of
meditation, which

00:38:05.090 --> 00:38:07.150
I think is important
to talk about because

00:38:07.150 --> 00:38:08.960
without solid
meditation training,

00:38:08.960 --> 00:38:11.210
and because there's so many
misconceptions about it,

00:38:11.210 --> 00:38:13.600
most of us go into a
meditation practice, thinking,

00:38:13.600 --> 00:38:16.260
well, I have to give my
mind a command to stop.

00:38:16.260 --> 00:38:17.520
So then it looks like this.

00:38:17.520 --> 00:38:20.190
OK, brain, stop thinking.

00:38:20.190 --> 00:38:20.940
I'm hungry.

00:38:20.940 --> 00:38:22.200
Well, that was a thought.

00:38:22.200 --> 00:38:23.350
Now I'm thinking about
how I'm thinking.

00:38:23.350 --> 00:38:23.790
Oh, crap.

00:38:23.790 --> 00:38:24.670
Now I'm thinking
about how I'm thinking

00:38:24.670 --> 00:38:25.270
about how I'm thinking.

00:38:25.270 --> 00:38:26.070
And I quit.

00:38:26.070 --> 00:38:29.520
And I can never meditate
because my brain is too crazy.

00:38:29.520 --> 00:38:30.750
And I hear this all the time.

00:38:30.750 --> 00:38:32.730
You're like, Emily, I get it,
meditation is so good for you,

00:38:32.730 --> 00:38:34.521
everybody talks about
it, but I can't do it

00:38:34.521 --> 00:38:37.609
because my mind is crazy.

00:38:37.609 --> 00:38:40.150
We all think that we're the most
stressed person in the land.

00:38:40.150 --> 00:38:43.240
We all think that we're the
busiest person in the land.

00:38:43.240 --> 00:38:46.760
But the truth is that giving
your mind a command to stop

00:38:46.760 --> 00:38:48.130
is impossible.

00:38:48.130 --> 00:38:51.080
No one can give their
mind a command to stop.

00:38:51.080 --> 00:38:53.900
The mind thinks
involuntarily, just

00:38:53.900 --> 00:38:56.300
like the heart
beats involuntarily.

00:38:56.300 --> 00:38:58.810
So if you judge
yourself at how good you

00:38:58.810 --> 00:39:01.200
are at giving your
body a command

00:39:01.200 --> 00:39:03.501
to stop an involuntary
action, then you're

00:39:03.501 --> 00:39:05.000
always going to
feel like a failure,

00:39:05.000 --> 00:39:06.907
and you're going to quit
in like one weekend.

00:39:06.907 --> 00:39:08.490
And this is a big
part of what I teach

00:39:08.490 --> 00:39:10.130
in my course is that
I give you permission

00:39:10.130 --> 00:39:11.670
and let you know that
thoughts are not the enemy.

00:39:11.670 --> 00:39:13.295
Thoughts during
meditation are actually

00:39:13.295 --> 00:39:16.970
an indicator that stress
is leaving the body.

00:39:16.970 --> 00:39:19.580
So yes.

00:39:19.580 --> 00:39:22.500
Did that answer your question?

00:39:22.500 --> 00:39:23.400
Great.

