00:42:20.200 --> 00:42:21.600
or a mindfulness exercise.

00:42:26.080 --> 00:42:29.380
So as you inhale, it
could be a gentle inhale,

00:42:29.380 --> 00:42:33.100
but I want you to notice
the most predominant sound

00:42:33.100 --> 00:42:34.680
you can detect right now.

00:42:34.680 --> 00:42:36.705
So I just want you to
hear what you're hearing.

00:42:36.705 --> 00:42:37.580
It might be my voice.

00:42:37.580 --> 00:42:38.730
It might be the air conditioner.

00:42:38.730 --> 00:42:39.940
It might be your
neighbors breath.

00:42:39.940 --> 00:42:41.731
But just notice the
most predominant sound.

00:42:48.460 --> 00:42:50.960
And on your next breath, see
if you can shift your awareness

00:42:50.960 --> 00:42:54.180
to the most subtle sound.

00:42:54.180 --> 00:42:55.980
It could be the sound
of your own breath,

00:42:55.980 --> 00:42:58.271
or maybe your hair rustling
against your neck, or maybe

00:42:58.271 --> 00:42:59.530
a sound far away in the city.

00:43:08.740 --> 00:43:11.220
Now, keeping the eyes
closed, on your next breath,

00:43:11.220 --> 00:43:13.759
I want you to shift your
attention to your sight.

00:43:13.759 --> 00:43:15.300
So even with your
eyes closed, I want

00:43:15.300 --> 00:43:16.864
you to see what you're seeing.

00:43:16.864 --> 00:43:19.530
Perhaps you can notice the cells
floating in front of your eyes,

00:43:19.530 --> 00:43:21.460
or perhaps you can see where
the light is streaming in

00:43:21.460 --> 00:43:22.530
through your eyelids.

00:43:22.530 --> 00:43:25.340
But just allow yourself
to see what you're seeing.

00:43:25.340 --> 00:43:27.560
This technique is called
come to your senses.

00:43:27.560 --> 00:43:30.060
We're going to work through
all five of our senses,

00:43:30.060 --> 00:43:32.280
noticing the most predominant
and the most subtle.

00:43:39.690 --> 00:43:41.630
And on your next inhale,
allow your awareness

00:43:41.630 --> 00:43:46.111
to gently rest on the most
predominant tactile sensation.

00:43:46.111 --> 00:43:47.610
For most of us,
since we're sitting,

00:43:47.610 --> 00:43:50.590
it'll probably be
your bum in the chair.

00:43:50.590 --> 00:43:52.910
Or perhaps you have
a pain in your knee,

00:43:52.910 --> 00:43:54.944
or you have a tickle
in your throat.

00:43:54.944 --> 00:43:57.443
Just notice whatever that most
predominant tactile sensation

00:43:57.443 --> 00:43:57.943
is.

00:44:03.850 --> 00:44:10.707
And on your next inhale, see if
you can notice the most subtle.

00:44:10.707 --> 00:44:12.540
This might be as subtle
as the breath coming

00:44:12.540 --> 00:44:13.770
in and out of your nostrils.

00:44:13.770 --> 00:44:18.460
It might be as subtle as the
hair on the back of your neck.

00:44:18.460 --> 00:44:20.997
Really tuning your
attention to the more subtle

00:44:20.997 --> 00:44:21.830
physical sensations.

00:44:32.390 --> 00:44:34.500
And now, on your
next breath, I want

00:44:34.500 --> 00:44:36.200
you to taste what
you're tasting.

00:44:36.200 --> 00:44:38.600
Even though you're not
eating anything currently,

00:44:38.600 --> 00:44:40.300
perhaps you can
taste your mouth wash

00:44:40.300 --> 00:44:42.950
from this morning or the coffee
that you drink beforehand

00:44:42.950 --> 00:44:45.590
or the lunch that you had.

00:44:45.590 --> 00:44:47.495
Maybe your mouth
tastes acidic or dry,

00:44:47.495 --> 00:44:50.165
but just noticing that most
predominant taste sensation.

00:44:55.977 --> 00:44:57.435
And on your next
inhale, see if you

00:44:57.435 --> 00:44:59.268
can shift your awareness
to the most subtle.

00:45:03.311 --> 00:45:05.310
And if you're not tasting
anything, that's fine.

00:45:05.310 --> 00:45:06.860
Just notice that.

00:45:06.860 --> 00:45:09.851
There's no right or wrong here.

00:45:09.851 --> 00:45:11.350
Now, on your next
inhale, I want you

00:45:11.350 --> 00:45:12.692
to smell what you're smelling.

00:45:12.692 --> 00:45:15.150
I want you to smell the most
predominant smell in the room.

00:45:15.150 --> 00:45:18.050
It might be your own hairspray
or your neighbor's lunch

00:45:18.050 --> 00:45:19.511
or who knows.

00:45:19.511 --> 00:45:22.010
But just allow yourself to smell
the most predominant smell.

00:45:26.510 --> 00:45:28.892
And now, shift it
to the most subtle.

00:45:28.892 --> 00:45:31.100
So maybe it's the fact that
you don't smell anything,

00:45:31.100 --> 00:45:33.308
or how does this room smell
different than your home?

00:45:38.331 --> 00:45:38.830
Really good.

00:45:38.830 --> 00:45:40.040
And on your next
breath, I want you

00:45:40.040 --> 00:45:41.740
to see if you can
allow your awareness

00:45:41.740 --> 00:45:44.780
to rest on all five
senses at the same time.

00:45:44.780 --> 00:45:48.430
So enjoying your sense of
hearing, your sense of touch,

00:45:48.430 --> 00:45:50.460
your sense of sight,
your sense of taste,

00:45:50.460 --> 00:45:53.960
and your sense of smell,
all simultaneously.

00:45:53.960 --> 00:45:55.760
Awakening all five
senses in the body,

00:45:55.760 --> 00:45:57.940
jettisoning yourself
into your right brain

00:45:57.940 --> 00:46:01.034
and therefore,
into the right now.

00:46:01.034 --> 00:46:03.450
And the truth is, if you can
bring yourself into the right

00:46:03.450 --> 00:46:05.310
now, the truth is you are fine.

00:46:05.310 --> 00:46:07.601
Every single one of us
are drowning in abundance.

00:46:07.601 --> 00:46:09.600
You have a place to sleep,
you have food to eat,

00:46:09.600 --> 00:46:11.115
you have people who love you.

00:46:11.115 --> 00:46:13.960
We just need to bring our
awareness into the right now.

00:46:18.400 --> 00:46:20.930
So now, take a nice, deep
inhale, and just exhaling

00:46:20.930 --> 00:46:22.930
any extraneous stress.

00:46:22.930 --> 00:46:24.630
I want you to try
a silent meditation

00:46:24.630 --> 00:46:26.125
